<paragraph blockId="73.[189,1399,452,621]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
Species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Thuy, 2013" authorityName="Thuy" authorityYear="2013" box="[319,440,452,478]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiacanthidae" genus="Geromura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[319,440,452,478]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Geromura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[448,556,452,478]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
with moderately large LAPs, at least twice wider than high; displaying two conspicuous, well-defined and strongly protruding spurs on the outer proximal edge paralleled by two poorly defined areas of densely meshed stereom on the inner distal edge; up to three spine articulations; single large knob in proximal LAPs, divided into two widely separate, smaller knobs in median and distal LAPs.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
